text:
East 35th Street, at the N.E. corner of Second Ave. Also shown is Second Ave., east side, north from East 35th Street. Across St. Gabriel's Park, is seen on East 37th Street, (left to right), the St. Gabriel's Branch of the New York Public Library, St. Gabriel's Hall and the Parochial School of St. Gabriel's R.C. Church. (Spire of church shown, which is located on East 38th Street).

June 6, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

35th Street, north side, west from end including Second Avenue: aerial view.

September 10, 1929.

P. L. Sperr.

Second Ave., east side, south from East 37th to and including 35th Streets. Note the hand ball courts in St. Gabriel's Park, that are under construction by the W.P.A.

April 8, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

Second Avenue, at East 35th Street, as photographed from atop the St. Gabriel's branch of the New York Public Library at No. 30 East 36th Street.

To the left are the handball courts in the western portion of St. Gabriels Park. The Second Avenue "El" darkens the roadbed. It's 34th Street station barely appears at the margin. In the background, at Madison Square are the distinctive buildings of the Metropolitan and the New York Life Insurance Co's.

Gift of Beecher Ogden
September, 1939

Second Avenue, west side, north from E. 35th Street:

January 7, 1939

Somach Photo Service
New York City

Second Avenue, east side, north from E. 35th Street, showing in the foreground the westerly portion of St. Gabriel's Park. Across same and appearing on the north side of 35th Street are the Library, Hall and Parochial School of the same name. The church spire is in the center, atop the church which faces on the south side of 37th Street. In the distant background are ornate structures forming Tudor City.

January 7, 1939

Somach Photo Service
New York City Tunnel Authority

1-West 35th Street looking westwards from and under cover of 2nd Avenue "El". Tower of Empire State building shown in distant.
2-35th Street, southeast corner and Lexington Avenue.

P.L. Sperr
View 1: July 23, 1939
View 2: October 11, 1939

1-West 35th Street looking westwards from and under cover of 2nd Avenue "El". Tower of Empire State building shown in distant.
2-35th Street, southeast corner and Lexington Avenue.

P.L. Sperr
View 1: July 23, 1939
View 2: October 11, 1939

E. 35th Street, east from Second Avenue to the East River, showing buildings on the south side of this thoroughfare facing St. Gabriel's Park. Slightly east of the Avenue is the four story building housing The Institute of Public Administration of Columbia University (No. 302-306). This formerly housed the College of Dental and Oral Surgery and which now occupies a new structure on 34th Street.

To the left margin appears the shadowy outline of the New York Steam Co. plant that is between First Avenue and the river. Across the latter is the triple chimneyed American Sugar Refining Co. plant in Greenpoint, Brooklyn.

January 7, 1939

Somach Photo Service
New York City Tunnel Authority

E. 35th Street, east of Second Avenue, showing mainly the southerly side of St. Gabriel's Park. This occupy an entire square block between 35th and 36th Streets, and First and Second Avenues. Diagonally thru the upper portion (foreground) of the area will run the underground approach to the 38th Street tunnel, necessitating the entire demolition of buildings show n at the left center. These occupy the frontage on the north side of 36th Street, between the aforementioned Avenues. To the right, is the New York Steam Co. plant at the East River's edge.

January 7, 1939
Somach Photo Service
New York City Tunnel Authority

E. 35th street, at adjoining and cast of the S. E. cornet of Second Avenue (right) as viewed south-westward, showing mainly the original College of Dental and Oral Surgery  (Colombia University). A new building was later erected on 34th Street and joined with this at the rear, this becoming the Institute of Public Administration

January 12, 1939

Somuch Photo Service
New York City Tunnel Authority

West 35th Street, north side, west from Second Avenue.

January 7, 1939

Somach Photo Service
New York City Tunnel Authority

E. 35th Street, south side, west from Second Avenue. Absent at this date are two four story dwellings that bore No's 244-6 E. 35th Street. The corner structure is under improvement in July of this year. Dimly outlined in the distance is the huge Empire State Building.

January 7, 1939

Somach Photo Service
New York City Tunnel Authority

E. 35th Street, south side, east from Third to Second Avenues. Overhead is the roadbed of the Third Avenue "El".

January 7, 1939

Somach Photo Service
New Your City Tunnel Authority

Second Avenue, east side, from East 35th to 37th Streets, showing St. Gabriels Park (35th-36th Streets), and the Midtown Queens Tunnel Plaza (36th-37th Streets). Both of these open areas extend to First Avenue. The buildings shown are on the eastside of same and the north side of E. 37th Street. Both of these photos are taken from a passing 2nd Avenue "El" train.

Second Avenue, east side, from East 35th to 37th Streets, showing St. Gabriels Park (35th-36th Streets), and the Midtown Queens Tunnel Plaza (36th-37th Streets). East 35th Street, north side, east of Second Avenue, showing the cut-thru St. Gabriels Park leading to the Midtown-Queens Tunnel. The buildings in the background are on the north side of East 37th Street. Second Avenue is on the left. This thoroughfare appears in View 2 with its darkening "El" and the dominant Chrysler and News Buildings overshadowing same.
